&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Madurai, Ludhiana, and Chennai.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Swachh Survekshan 2025 report ranked Madurai, Ludhiana, and Chennai as the top three dirtiest cities in India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Madurai&lt;/strong&gt; topped the list of India&amp;rsquo;s dirtiest cities in 2025 with a score of 4,823, followed by &lt;strong&gt;Ludhiana (5,272)&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Chennai (6,822)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;The rankings are part of the &lt;strong&gt;Swachh Survekshan 2025&lt;/strong&gt; assessment under the &lt;strong&gt;Swachh Bharat Mission&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Metros such as &lt;strong&gt;Bengaluru (5th), Ranchi (4th)&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Delhi (10th)&lt;/strong&gt; also featured among the dirtiest cities, indicating urban cleanliness challenges.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Smaller cities and towns like &lt;strong&gt;Ahmedabad, Bhopal, Raipur, and Jabalpur&lt;/strong&gt; outperformed major metros, highlighting better local governance and waste management.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Top 10 Dirtiest Cities in India (Swachh Survekshan 2025)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;1. Madurai &amp;ndash; 4,823&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;2. Ludhiana &amp;ndash; 5,272&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;3. Chennai &amp;ndash; 6,822&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;4. Ranchi &amp;ndash; 6,835&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;5. Bengaluru &amp;ndash; 6,842&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;6. Dhanbad &amp;ndash; 7,196&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;7. Faridabad &amp;ndash; 7,329&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;8. Greater Mumbai &amp;ndash; 7,419&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;9. Srinagar &amp;ndash; 7,488&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;10. Delhi &amp;ndash; 7,920&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clean City Performers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indore, Surat, and Navi Mumbai&lt;/strong&gt; were recognised in the &amp;ldquo;Super Swachh League&amp;rdquo; for consistent cleanliness.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Smaller towns showcased effective &lt;strong&gt;waste segregation, sanitation infrastructure, and citizen participation&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Swachh Survekshan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the world&amp;rsquo;s largest urban cleanliness survey conducted under the &lt;strong&gt;Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Assesses cities on parameters such as waste management, public sanitation, and citizen feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to drive healthy competition among urban local bodies for a cleaner India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

