&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kavach Automatic Train Protection&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kavach Automatic Train Protection (ATP)&lt;/strong&gt; is an &lt;strong&gt;indigenous railway safety system&lt;/strong&gt; developed by the Indian Railways to enhance train safety and prevent accidents such as collisions and derailments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The implementation of the &lt;strong&gt;Kavach system&lt;/strong&gt; is a significant milestone in the Indian Railways&amp;#39; efforts to modernize its infrastructure and improve safety. By &lt;strong&gt;2025&lt;/strong&gt;, the system is planned to cover a distance of &lt;strong&gt;3,500 km&lt;/strong&gt; at a cost of &lt;strong&gt;₹1,700 crore&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Kavach system uses &lt;strong&gt;state-of-the-art technologies&lt;/strong&gt; like signals passed at danger (SPAD), automatic braking in case of driver error, and real-time communication between the train and signaling systems to ensure the highest level of safety.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was successfully tested on &lt;strong&gt;March 4, 2022&lt;/strong&gt;, with a demonstration attended by the &lt;strong&gt;Union Minister of Railways, Ashwini Vaishnaw&lt;/strong&gt;, showcasing its effectiveness in preventing accidents.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Indian government aims to expand the Kavach system to cover the entire railway network, ensuring the safety of passengers and reducing risks associated with human errors in train operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Features of Kavach System:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automatic Braking:&lt;/strong&gt; The Kavach system automatically applies brakes to prevent collisions in case the train overshoots a signal or encounters another train on the same track.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SPAD (Signals Passed at Danger):&lt;/strong&gt; It ensures that the train halts before passing a danger signal, thereby averting potential accidents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Real-Time Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; The system allows real-time communication between trains and station signaling systems to provide updates on movement and track conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indigenous Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Kavach is a &lt;strong&gt;Make in India initiative&lt;/strong&gt;, developed by Indian Railways, which ensures cost-effectiveness and promotes local manufacturing capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of Kavach:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It aims to reduce human errors, which are a leading cause of train accidents in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Kavach is expected to significantly enhance passenger safety and improve the efficiency of train operations on Indian railways.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;As part of the modernization drive, the Indian Railways plans to implement this system across its high-density routes and ensure safer and faster travel for passengers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comparison with Other Options:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nationwide Railway Safety System:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a generic term and does not refer to any specific system implemented by Indian Railways.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Namo Bharat Signalling System:&lt;/strong&gt; No such system exists in Indian Railways under this name.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GPS-based Tracking System:&lt;/strong&gt; While GPS technology is used for tracking trains, it is not a comprehensive safety system like Kavach, which includes automatic braking and SPAD features.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Future Plans:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Indian Railways has set a target to implement the Kavach system across &lt;strong&gt;34,000 km of its network&lt;/strong&gt;, focusing on high-density routes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The initiative aligns with the government&amp;#39;s vision of achieving high levels of safety and reliability in the railway sector.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 233.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Supreme Court delivered its judgment regarding the eligibility for direct recruitment as District Judges under Article 233 of the Indian Constitution.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Court ruled that judicial officers with seven years of prior experience as advocates are eligible for direct recruitment as District Judges under Article 233.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 233(2) mentions qualifications for advocates but does not specify separate qualifications for in-service judicial officers, which led to this clarification by the Court.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The judgment allows for in-service judicial officers with 7 years of practice as advocates before joining the judicial service to be considered for direct recruitment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The appointment of District Judges is done by the Governor after consulting the High Court, ensuring judicial independence in the process.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Article 233&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Article 233 deals with the appointment of District Judges by the Governor, after consulting the High Court, and provides the framework for qualifications for direct recruitment in the judiciary.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Judicial Officers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In-service judicial officers with a minimum of seven years of practice as advocates are now eligible for direct appointment as District Judges based on this Supreme Court ruling.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;High Court Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The High Court plays a critical role in the appointment process for District Judges, ensuring judicial independence in selection procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

